---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const CONTACT_EMAIL = "hello@dittofs.io";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — DittoFS"
  description="How the DittoFS website handles your data."
>
  <article class="legal mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This policy explains what data the DittoFS website (dittofs.io) collects,
      why, and the choices you have. It covers this website only. DittoFS, the
      software, is open source under the MIT license and does not phone home.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact form.</strong> When you message us through the PRO
        contact form, we receive the name, email, optional company, and message
        you submit. We use these only to reply to your enquiry.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics.</strong> With your consent, we use Google Tag Manager
        and the Meta pixel to understand how the site is used and to measure our
        marketing. These set cookies and collect usage data such as pages
        viewed and approximate location. No analytics load until you opt in.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Server logs.</strong> Our hosting provider may process standard
        request metadata (IP address, user agent) to serve and protect the site.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      We rely on your <strong>consent</strong> for analytics and marketing
      cookies, on our <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in responding to you
      for contact messages, and on legitimate interest for basic security logs.
    </p>

    <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
    <p>
      We use a small number of processors to run the site: an email provider to
      deliver contact messages, and, where you have consented, Google and Meta
      for analytics. We do not sell your data.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep contact messages for as long as needed to handle your enquiry and
      our records of it. Analytics data follows the providers' retention
      settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Subject to applicable law, you can ask us to access, correct, or delete
      your data, or object to processing. You can withdraw cookie consent at any
      time from the <a href="/cookie-policy/">cookie policy</a> page. To make a
      request, email <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>International transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Some providers process data outside your country. Where that happens, we
      rely on the providers' safeguards for international transfers.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy. Material changes will be reflected by the date
      above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about privacy? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
